---
// src/pages/reviews/sony-wh-1000xm6-review.astro
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Sony WH-1000XM6 Review 2026 - Still the ANC King?">
  <article class="review">
    <header class="review-header">
      <span class="category">Audio</span>
      <h1>Sony WH-1000XM6 Review: Still the ANC King in 2026?</h1>
      <div class="meta">
        <span>By Alice AI</span>
        <span>•</span>
        <span>March 11, 2026</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="rating">
      <span class="score">4.8</span>
      <span class="stars">⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐</span>
    </div>

    <div class="toc">
      <h2>Table of Contents</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="#overview">Overview</a></li>
        <li><a href="#anc">Noise Cancellation</a></li>
        <li><a href="#sound">Sound Quality</a></li>
        <li><a href="#design">Design & Comfort</a></li>
        <li><a href="#battery">Battery & Charging</a></li>
        <li><a href="#verdict">Verdict</a></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>Sony's WH-1000X series has long been the benchmark for noise-canceling headphones. The new WH-1000XM6 aims to maintain that lead with a new dual-processor design and ultra-comfortable materials. After two weeks of testing, here's our deep dive.</p>
      
      <div class="pros-cons">
        <div class="pros">
          <h3>Pros</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>✅ Industry-leading noise cancellation</li>
            <li>✅ Incredible 45-hour battery life</li>
            <li>✅ Foldable design returns!</li>
            <li>✅ Spatial Audio with head tracking is superb</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="cons">
          <h3>Cons</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>❌ Multipoint connection can still be finicky</li>
            <li>❌ Microphone quality in wind is only average</li>
            <li>❌ Price has increased to $399</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="anc">
      <h2>Noise Cancellation</h2>
      <p>The XM6 introduces the "HD Noise Canceling Processor QN2." In our testing, it effectively silenced the low rumble of airplane engines and the high-pitched chatter of a busy cafe. It feels like stepping into a private room whenever you put them on.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="sound">
      <h2>Sound Quality</h2>
      <p>Sony has refined the sound signature, offering a tighter bass and more detailed highs. Supporting LDAC and the new LC3+ codec, the XM6 delivers near-lossless audio wirelessly. The EQ in the Sony Headphones app remains the best in the business.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="design">
      <h2>Design & Comfort</h2>
      <p>Great news: the XM6 is foldable again! This makes them much easier to pack than the XM5. The earcups use a new "Soft Fit" leather that feels significantly cooler during long listening sessions.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="battery">
      <h2>Battery & Charging</h2>
      <p>We consistently achieved 45 hours of playback with ANC on. Quick charging is also impressive—just 3 minutes of charging gives you 5 hours of playback time via USB-C PD.</p>
    </section>

    <section id="verdict">
      <h2>Verdict</h2>
      <p>The Sony WH-1000XM6 is the most complete pair of headphones we've ever tested. While the price is steep, the combination of top-tier ANC, great sound, and a foldable design makes them the easy choice for frequent travelers and audiophiles alike.</p>
      
      <div class="buy-links">
        <h3>Where to Buy</h3>
        <a href="https://www.amazon.com/dp/SONYXM6?tag=rc0440-20" class="buy-btn" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">
          Check Price on Amazon
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .review {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 2rem;
    background: white;
  }

  .review-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .category {
    background: #000000;
    color: white;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 20px;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
  }

  .review-header h1 {
    font-size: 2.5rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .meta {
    color: #666;
    display: flex;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .rating {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: #f8f9fa;
    border-radius: 12px;
  }

  .score {
    font-size: 3rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #000000;
  }

  .stars {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-left: 1rem;
  }

  .toc {
    background: #f8f9fa;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .toc h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .toc ul {
    list-style: none;
  }

  .toc li {
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
  }

  .toc a {
    color: #000000;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 2px solid transparent;
  }

  .toc a:hover {
    border-bottom: 2px solid #000000;
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  section h2 {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: #333;
  }

  section p {
    color: #555;
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .pros-cons {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .pros, .cons {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
  }

  .pros {
    background: #e8f5e9;
  }

  .cons {
    background: #ffebee;
  }

  .pros h3, .cons h3 {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .pros ul, .cons ul {
    list-style: none;
  }

  .pros li, .cons li {
    padding: 0.5rem 0;
  }

  .buy-links {
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    background: #f8f9fa;
    border-radius: 12px;
  }

  .buy-btn {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 1rem 3rem;
    background: #ff9900;
    color: white;
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 8px;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .buy-btn:hover {
    background: #e68a00;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .pros-cons {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    
    .review-header h1 {
      font-size: 1.75rem;
    }
  }
</style>
